changes.value:
**File:** `kanban-app/ui/src/lib/entity-commands.ts:77,126`

```ts
if (cmd.id === "entity.inspect") {
  inspect?.(entityMoniker);
}
```

Hardcodes that `entity.inspect` is the one command handled client-side instead of dispatched to Rust. Also in `focus-scope.tsx:119` which hardcodes resolving `entity.inspect` for double-click. Commands should declare their execution mode (client vs backend) in the schema rather than being special-cased by ID.

